sentences: Robert John Godfrey (born 30 July 1947) is a British composer, pianist and a founding member of The Enid.
From 1968 to 1971 Godfrey became resident musical director with Barclay James Harvest, making musical contributions to early recordings which established their full, orchestral style of rock music.
In 1974 the Charisma Records label released his first solo album, Fall of Hyperion.
Godfrey was the winner of the Visionary award at the 2014 Progressive Music Awards.
In 2016, he retired from playing with The Enid due to his illness.
His last regular performance with the band took place on 2 April 2016.

However, in June 2017, it was announced that Godfrey would be joining The Enid in August of that year to celebrate his 70th birthday with a one-off performance at the Union Chapel in London, that took place on 5 August.
